def: The fourth power, or the square of the square. Thus 4x4=16, thesquare of 4, and 16x16=256, the biquadrate of 4.
In the sense or manner of a participle.
The act of evincing or proving, or the state of being evinced.
A dark brown substance of vegetable origin, allied to curare,and used by the natives of New Granada as an arrow poison.
The act or art precipitating a metal electro-chemical action,by which a coating is deposited, on a prepared surface, as inelectroplating and electrotyping; galvanoplasty.
Act of making gestures; gesturing. [Obs.] Bp. Hall.
An antithetic or contrasted statement. Bacon.
A plant coif or skullcap. Same as Calotte. B. Jonson.
